Here is a step by step guide to start controlling your De'Longhi Pinguino with Alexa: 
(1). Download ""De'Longhi Comfort"" app in Google Play or iOS App Store;
(2). Launch the app and register a new account (or login if you’re already registered);
(3). Turn on your De'Longhi Pinguino and connect it with ""De'Longhi Comfort"" app;
(4) You can rename your Pinguino with De'Longhi Comfort App. In this way, Alexa will recognise the device with that name.
(5). Download Amazon ""Alexa"" app from Google Play or iOS App Store, and connect your smart speaker with ""Alexa"" app;
(6). Search the Alexa Skills directory for ""De'Longhi Pinguino Portable Air Conditioner"";
(7). Click Enable skill, then input your account username, password and region on the linking page;
(8). Finalise the device discovery in Alexa app. You can also say ""Alexa, discover devices.”. Wait till Alexa says ""Discover is completed"";
(9). Now all setup is done and you can start talking to Alexa to control your De'Longhi Pinguino Portable Air Conditioner"

These are some of the voice commands you are enabled to: 
Alexa, turn on the [AC] 
Alexa, turn off the [AC] 
Alexa, set the [AC] to 20 degrees
Alexa, increase the [AC] temperature
Alexa, decrease the [AC] temperature
Alexa, what is the [AC] temperature?
Alexa, set the fan to auto on [AC]
